oai_dc:dc.dc:title: the Vets Corner: CANARY POX
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Cooper, Ralph
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: It seems that canary pox has comealong to displace Newcastle Disease andpsittacosis from the center of attentionamong local breeders. There is no doubtthat it can cause a disaster among infectedflocks, but there are some positivemeasures which can be taken to minimizeits impact. Because it is always helpfulto understand the true nature of adisease in order that rational and effectivemeasures may be taken to prevent itsspread and minimize the losses, I wouldlike to discuss the disease in some detail.
